What are Java Annotations?
- Special labels/markers added to Java classes
- Provide meta-data abut the class
- Processes at compile time or run-time for special processing

Scanning for Component Classes
- Spring will can your Java classes for special annotations
- automatically register the beans in the Spring container

Development Process
1. Enable component scannig in Spring config file
  <context:component-scan base-package="<package>" />
2. Add the @Component Annotation to your Java classes
3. Retrieve bean from Spring container


Default Bean Id
- the class name, make first letter lower-case